citeinfo.title: Kern County Crop Boundaries (2016)

descript.abstract: The Kern County Department of Agriculture and Measurement Standards created this dataset to more precisely locate production agricultural field boundaries within the county.
descript.purpose: The Department of Agriculture and Measurement Standards issues annual permits to growers who intend to apply restricted materials to commercial crop locations. Each grower must hold a current permit before he/she can purchase these materials. California regulations require that maps of cropland for which the grower is responsible be included in this permitting process. This dataset helps the department assess each site for California Environmental Quality Act (CEQA) equivalency, proximity to sensitive areas, create standardized maps for all sites, and compile a history of land use for Kern County.

attr.attrdef: Internal feature number.

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: Feature geometry.

Permit - Uniquely identifies an individual grower through time. Each grower maintains the same permit number from year to year. First time permittees obtain a new, never before used permit number in order to avoid same values that reference different growers through time.

Site Identification - Uniquely identifies each permitted site (polygon) on a grower permit. This value will not be duplicated on the same permit in the same year. These values may be used again from year to year by a permittee but may not always reference the same piece of ground from year to year (i.e. Site ID 122A may be referenced on an individual permit over many years, but may not always refer to the same piece of ground each year).
Primary Status - Defines whether a polygon is (A)ctive or i(N)active.

Secondary Status - Defines whether a polygon is (A) single permitted site at one time, an (I)nterplanted site in which there are exactly two commodities permitted for the same piece of ground at the same time (First used in 2002), or a (M)ultiple site in which there are three or more commodities permitted for the same piece of ground at the same time (First used in 2005). The (M) designation is used to generally define a piece of ground with numerous very small (<1 acre) intermingled vegetable crop sites.
Date Activated - Polygon addition date.
Commodity - Common name for the permitted crop represented by this polygon.
Operator Activated - Inspector who added the polygon to the database.
Date Inactivated - Date the polygon (site) was replaced by another polygon (site) or December 31st for sites active at the end of the calendar year.
Operator Inactivated - Inspector who archived the polygon.
Township – Public Land Survey System (PLSS) Township.
Range – Public Land Survey System (PLSS) Range.
Section – Public Land Survey (PLSS) Section.
Agent Name – Primary permit holder's name.
Permittee – Farming entity name.
Mailing Address – Primary permit holder's address or farm headquarters.
Mailing State – Primary permit holder's state.
Mailing Zip – Primary permit holder's zip code.
Mailing City – Primary permit holder's city.
Permit-Site - Concatenated value which serves as the unique identifier for each polygon in this database.
Acres Permitted – Grower-provided net planted acres for the site.
Permit Year – Calendar year for which the polygon is active. Inspectors begin issuing annual permits in December of the previous year and sometimes enter polygons after the end of the calendar year.
